dmiClassTable.name: dmiClassTable
dmiClassTable.description: The MIF definitions for all group classes known to the Service Layer.

dmiClassEntry.name: dmiClassEntry
dmiClassEntry.description: The meta-data defining a particular group class. If multiple versions of a particular group class are registered with the Service Layer, the data in this entry shall pertain to the highest version.

dmiClassIndex.name: dmiClassIndex
dmiClassIndex.description: A unique value for each group class known to the mapping agent for this managed node. The value for each class must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the mapping agent to the next re-initialization. This value is NOT necessarily equal to the Group ID assigned within a given Component by the DMI Service Layer.

dmiClassString.name: dmiClassString
dmiClassString.description: The 'class string' assigned to the group in the 'class' statement.

dmiClassVersion.name: dmiClassVersion
dmiClassVersion.description: The version number of the group definition providing it appeared as an integer in the 'class string'; zero otherwise.

dmiClassName.name: dmiClassName
dmiClassName.description: The 'group name' from the 'name' statement in the group definition.

dmiClassOID.name: dmiClassOID
dmiClassOID.description: The OBJECT IDENTIFIER of the conceptual table representing the group in an SNMP MIB. Attributes of the group may be accessed as columnar objects of this table, indexed according to the rules specified in RFC-nnnn.

dmiClassKeyCount.name: dmiClassKeyCount
dmiClassKeyCount.description: The number attributes that comprise a key for this group; zero if no 'key' statement appeared in the group definition. The ordered list of attribute Id's that comprise the key can be obtained from the dmiKeyTable

dmiClassDescrLength.name: dmiClassDescrLength
dmiClassDescrLength.description: The total length (in octets) of the 'description string' from the 'description' statement in the group definition. This string can be retrieved in segments from the dmiDescrTable

dmiClassPragma.name: dmiClassPragma
dmiClassPragma.description: The 'group name' from the 'name' statement in the group definition.

dmiAttributeTable.name: dmiAttributeTable
dmiAttributeTable.description: A table listing all the meta-data for all attributes of each registered group class.

dmiAttributeEntry.name: dmiAttributeEntry
dmiAttributeEntry.description: The meta-data defining a particular DMI attribute.

dmiAttrId.name: dmiAttrId
dmiAttrId.description: The value of the 'id' statement from the attribute definition. This value uniquely identifies this attribute within the group.

dmiAttrName.name: dmiAttrName
dmiAttrName.description: The value of the 'name' statement from the attribute definition. This name is normally used for display to human users.

dmiAttrAccess.name: dmiAttrAccess
dmiAttrAccess.description: The value of the 'access' statement from the attribute definition. This value defines how the attribute may be accessed.

dmiAttrType.name: dmiAttrType
dmiAttrType.description: This is the value of the 'type' statement from the attribute definition. This value specifies the datatype of the attribute.

dmiAttrMaxSize.name: dmiAttrMaxSize
dmiAttrMaxSize.description: For string types, this value specifies the maximum number of octets that may be contained in the string. Zero implies no limit specified (or a non-string datatype).

dmiAttrEnumListCount.name: dmiAttrEnumListCount
dmiAttrEnumListCount.description: The number of name-value pairs in any associated enumeration list. Zero if not an enumerated integer.

dmiAttrDescrLength.name: dmiAttrDescrLength
dmiAttrDescrLength.description: The total length (in octets) of the 'description string' from the 'description' statement in the group definition. This string can be retrieved in segments from the dmiDescrTable

dmiKeyTable.name: dmiKeyTable
dmiKeyTable.description: A table of key definitions for each group that has a 'key' statement.

dmiKeyEntry.name: dmiKeyEntry
dmiKeyEntry.description: An entry in this table specifies an attribute that is (part of) the 'key' for the corresponding group.

dmiKeyIndex.name: dmiKeyIndex
dmiKeyIndex.description: An ordinal that indicates this attributes position in the key for this group.

dmiKeyType.name: dmiKeyType
dmiKeyType.description: The type of the attribute that forms this portion of the group key.

dmiKeyAttrId.name: dmiKeyAttrId
dmiKeyAttrId.description: The Id of the attribute that forms this portion of the group key.

dmiDescrTable.name: dmiDescrTable
dmiDescrTable.description: A table of description string segments. This table allows long description strings to be retrieved in segments. A complete description string can be reconstituted by concatenating the ordered set of string segments. The length of the complete string is available through the dmiClassTable or dmiAttributeTable as appropriate.

dmiDescrEntry.name: dmiDescrEntry
dmiDescrEntry.description: An entry in the description table contains one segment of an attribute or group description. The complete description string can be reconstituted by concatenating the ordered set of string segments. The length of the complete string is available through the dmiClassTable or dmiAttributeTable as appropriate. The description string for the group definition is accessed by specifying dmiAttrId==0

dmiDescrIndex.name: dmiDescrIndex
dmiDescrIndex.description: An ordinal that indicates this segment's relative position in the complete description string for this attribute or group.

dmiDescrText.name: dmiDescrText
dmiDescrText.description: A segment of the description string for this attribute or group.

dmiEnumTable.name: dmiEnumTable
dmiEnumTable.description: A table defining all enumerated lists known to the Service Layer.

dmiEnumEntry.name: dmiEnumEntry
dmiEnumEntry.description: An entry in this table defines the pairing of a string with an integer value as part of an 'Enum' definition.

dmiEnumId.name: dmiEnumId
dmiEnumId.description: A unique value for each entry within a particular 'Enum' definition.

dmiEnumValue.name: dmiEnumValue
dmiEnumValue.description: The integer value that is associated with the corresponding string (dmiEnumString).

dmiEnumString.name: dmiEnumString
dmiEnumString.description: The displayable string that is associated with the corresponding integer value (dmiEnumValue)

dmiComponentTable.name: dmiComponentTable
dmiComponentTable.description: A list of all components registered with the Service Layer.

dmiComponentEntry.name: dmiComponentEntry
dmiComponentEntry.description: An entry in this table describes a particular component registered with the Service Layer

dmiCompId.name: dmiCompId
dmiCompId.description: The unique Id assigned to the component by the Service Layer at registration time. By convention, the Service Layer itself will have an Id of one.

dmiCompName.name: dmiCompName
dmiCompName.description: The value of the 'name' statement from the component definition block.

dmiCompDescrLength.name: dmiCompDescrLength
dmiCompDescrLength.description: The total length of the component description string in octets.

dmiCompGroupCount.name: dmiCompGroupCount
dmiCompGroupCount.description: The number of group instances contained within this component.

dmiCompPragma.name: dmiCompPragma
dmiCompPragma.description: The value of the 'pragama' statement from the component definition block.

dmiCompDescrTable.name: dmiCompDescrTable
dmiCompDescrTable.description: A table of description string segments. This table allows long description strings to be retrieved in segments. A complete description string can be reconstituted by concatenating the ordered set of string segments. The length of the complete string is available through the dmiComponentTable.

dmiCompDescrEntry.name: dmiCompDescrEntry
dmiCompDescrEntry.description: An entry in the description table contains one segment of a component description. The complete description string can be reconstituted by concatenating the ordered set of string segments. The length of the complete string is available through the dmiComponentTable.

dmiCompDescrIndex.name: dmiCompDescrIndex
dmiCompDescrIndex.description: An ordinal that indicates this segment's relative position in the complete description string for this attribute or group.

dmiCompDescrText.name: dmiCompDescrText
dmiCompDescrText.description: A segment of the description string for this attribute or group.

dmiGroupTable.name: dmiGroupTable
dmiGroupTable.description: A list of all group instances contained within each component.

dmiGroupEntry.name: dmiGroupEntry
dmiGroupEntry.description: An entry in this table describes a particular group instance within a particular component.

dmiGroupId.name: dmiGroupId
dmiGroupId.description: An identifier assigned by the DMI Service Layer that uniquely identifies this group instance within a particular component.

dmiGroupClassString.name: dmiGroupClassString
dmiGroupClassString.description: The class string of the group (or table) instance as registered with the DMI Service Layer for the given component.

dmiGroupVersion.name: dmiGroupVersion
dmiGroupVersion.description: The version number of the group definition providing it appeared as an integer in the 'class string'; zero otherwise.

dmiGroupClassIndex.name: dmiGroupClassIndex
dmiGroupClassIndex.description: The index of the corresponding group class definition in the dmiClassTable. This index is an artifact of the mapping agent and serves as a cross-reference into the dmiClassTable for the remainder of the group class definition.

dmiLanguageTable.name: dmiLanguageTable
dmiLanguageTable.description: A list of all language bindings registered for each component.

dmiLanguageEntry.name: dmiLanguageEntry
dmiLanguageEntry.description: An entry in this table describes a particular language binding within a particular component.

dmiLanguage.name: dmiLanguage
dmiLanguage.description: The language string, defined by the DMI 2.0 Specification, that identifies a native language character set supported by the component. The format of the string is: 'language-code|territory-code|encoding' where language-code is one of the two-letter codes defined in ISO 639, territory-code is one of the two leteter codes defined in ISO 3166, and encoding is either 'iso8859-1' or 'unicode'.

dmiMappingLevel.name: dmiMappingLevel
dmiMappingLevel.description: The mapping level identifies the capabilities supported by the DMI-to-SNMP mapping agent. This object is defined as a bit-mask where each bit corresponds to a specific mapping capability. If the bit is '1', the capability is supported by the mapping agent. If the bit is '0', the capability is not supported. The mapping capabilities defined are: 0x01 Event Mapping Supported 0x02 Request/Response Mapping Supported 0x04 Row Addition/Deletion Supported 0x08 Remote Proxy Supported 0x10 Dynamic OID Generation Supported All other (unused) bits must be '0'. For example, a mapping agent that supports Event and Request/Response mapping, including Dynamic OID Generation, but does not support row addition/deletion nor remote proxy returns the value 0x13.

dmiEventType.name: dmiEventType
dmiEventType.reference: DMTF DMI 2.0 Specification, Section 3.2.2.2.1' class = 'EventGeneration|<specific name>|001' name = 'Event System', ID = 1
dmiEventType.description: Event-specific information that identifies the type of event within the DMI Event Generation group. Normally, this information is conveyed in the resulting SNMP Notification OID derived from the DMI Event to SNMP Trap mapping procedure. This object is not included in event specific traps. However, this object is defined for use within the generic dmiEventIndication trap, when mapping the DMI event to a specific SNMP trap is not possible (e.g., the DMI Class to SNMP OID mapping is not defined).

dmiEventSeverity.name: dmiEventSeverity
dmiEventSeverity.reference: DMTF DMI 2.0 Specification, Section 3.2.2.2.2' class = 'EventGeneration|<specific name>|001' name = 'Event Severity', ID = 2

dmiEventStateKey.name: dmiEventStateKey
dmiEventStateKey.reference: DMTF DMI 2.0 Specification, Section 3.2.2.2.3&4' class = 'EventGeneration|<specific name>|001' name = 'Event Is State-Based', ID = 3; and name = 'Event State Key', ID = 4
dmiEventStateKey.description: The index into the Event State group for the component generating this event, provided the event is state-based. The value -1 indicates the event is not state-based.

dmiEventAssociatedGroup.name: dmiEventAssociatedGroup
dmiEventAssociatedGroup.reference: DMTF DMI 2.0 Specification, Section 3.2.2.2.5' class = 'EventGeneration|<specific name>|001' name = 'Associated Group', ID = 5
dmiEventAssociatedGroup.description: The class string of the DMI group associated with this event.

dmiEventSystem.name: dmiEventSystem
dmiEventSystem.reference: DMTF DMI 2.0 Specification, Section 3.2.2.2.6' class = 'EventGeneration|<specific name>|001' name = 'Event System', ID = 6
dmiEventSystem.description: Event-specific information that identifies the functional system of the component that caused the event. Normally, SNMP Traps mapped from a DMI Event contain an event-specific definition of this attribute. This object is not included in event specific traps. However, this object is defined for use within the generic dmiEventIndication trap, when mapping the DMI event to a specific SNMP trap is not possible (e.g., the DMI Class to SNMP OID mapping is not defined).

dmiEventSubSystem.name: dmiEventSubSystem
dmiEventSubSystem.reference: DMTF DMI 2.0 Specification, Section 3.2.2.2.7' class = 'EventGeneration|<specific name>|001' name = 'Event Subsystem', ID = 7
dmiEventSubSystem.description: Event-specific information that identifies the functional sub-system of the component that caused the event. Normally, SNMP Traps mapped from a DMI Event contain an event-specific definition of this attribute. This object is not included in event specific traps. However, this object is defined for use within the generic dmiEventIndication trap, when mapping the DMI event to a specific SNMP trap is not possible (e.g., the DMI Class to SNMP OID mapping is not defined).

dmiEventSolution.name: dmiEventSolution
dmiEventSolution.reference: DMTF DMI 2.0 Specification, Section 3.2.2.3.1' class = 'EventGeneration|<specific name>|001' name = 'Event Solution', ID = 8
dmiEventSolution.description: Event-specific information that describes the solution to the problem that caused the event. Typically, SNMP Traps mapped from a DMI Event contain an event-specific definition of this attribute. This object is not included in event specific traps. However, this object is defined for use within the generic dmiEventIndication trap, when mapping the DMI event to a specific SNMP trap is not possible (e.g., the DMI Class to SNMP OID mapping is not defined).

dmiEventVendorMsg.name: dmiEventVendorMsg
dmiEventVendorMsg.reference: DMTF DMI 2.0 Specification, Section 3.2.2.3.3' class = 'EventGeneration|<specific name>|001' name = Event Message', ID = 10
dmiEventVendorMsg.description: Vendor specific message related to the event. This data may contain any displayable string (ISO 8859-1).

dmiEventVendorData.name: dmiEventVendorData
dmiEventVendorData.reference: DMTF DMI 2.0 Specification, Section 3.2.2.3.4' class = 'EventGeneration|<specific name>|001' name = Vendor Specific Data', ID = 11
dmiEventVendorData.description: Vendor specific data related to the event. This data may contain any arbitrary string of octets.

dmiEventDateTime.name: dmiEventDateTime
dmiEventDateTime.description: The timestamp attached to an event indication by the DMI Service Layer.

dmiEventClassString.name: dmiEventClassString
dmiEventClassString.description: The Event Group class string used, along with the event type, to uniquely identify the DMI Event when translated into the general dmiEventIndication trap format.

dmiEventSource.name: dmiEventSource
dmiEventSource.description: The transport address that identifies the originator of the DMI Event or Indication. The event may be forwarded by other Service Layers acting as intermediaries for the originator of the event, or the event may have originated on a system other than the local mapping agent. This variable binding is only included in DMI Events and Indications if the original source is a system other than where the SNMP/DMI mapping agent is operating. If the transport selector (e.g., UDP port or IPX socket) of an SNMP mapping agent running on the specified system is not known, a zero (0) value is to indicate that only the network address portion is known. Otherwise, the transport selector value may be used by management applications to send SNMP requests directly to the specified system.

dmiEventIndication.name: dmiEventIndication
dmiEventIndication.description: A DMI Event associated with a group within a DMI component has occurred. Normally, DMI Events are translated into event specific SNMP notifications instead of this generic notification. However, this generic notification is defined for cases when mapping the DMI event to a specific SNMP trap is not possible (e.g., the DMI Class to SNMP OID mapping is not defined).

dmiComponentAddedIndication.name: dmiComponentAddedIndication
dmiComponentAddedIndication.description: A new component has been installed into the DMI Service Layer.

dmiComponentDeletedIndication.name: dmiComponentDeletedIndication
dmiComponentDeletedIndication.description: An installed component has been uninstalled from the DMI Service Layer.

dmiLanguageAddedIndication.name: dmiLanguageAddedIndication
dmiLanguageAddedIndication.description: A new language binding has been added to a component in the DMI Service Layer.

dmiLanguageDeletedIndication.name: dmiLanguageDeletedIndication
dmiLanguageDeletedIndication.description: An existing language binding has been removed from a component in the DMI Service Layer.

dmiGroupAddedIndication.name: dmiGroupAddedIndication
dmiGroupAddedIndication.description: A new group has been added to a component in the DMI Service Layer.

dmiGroupDeletedIndication.name: dmiGroupDeletedIndication
dmiGroupDeletedIndication.description: An existing group has been removed from a component in the DMI Service Layer.

dmiNotificationsGroup.name: dmiNotificationsGroup
dmiNotificationsGroup.description: The notifications that an SNMP entity is required to implement.
